activemods:active_mods.name: Bestiary
activemods:active_mods.description:
Shift + Right Click a monster while in combat to open an overlay detailing their attack patterns. Right click again to close this overlay. You can disable requiring shift in the Main Menu -> Mods -> Bestiary -> Config menu.

Controller users can (hopefully) now target a monster (they will be rendered with the little yellow triangles around them if it's done correctly). Once a monster is targeted, you can press whatever button you use to open the draw pile (left trigger by default) to open the overlay. Press your cancel button (B on an xbox controller by default) to close the overlay. This is an experimental feature.

Please report any bugs you find by leaving a comment on the Workshop page or creating an issue on the Github page. Thanks!
activemods:active_mods.credits: Special thanks to ForgottenArbiter and the Spire Reference spreadsheet, which managed to cut down the information gathering to a mere 12 hours instead of being many more.

activemods:active_mods.name: Slay the Relics Exporter
activemods:active_mods.description:
This mod exports data to Slay the Relics Twitch extension. 

This mod in combination with the extension displays deck view and tooltips for viewers on stream for relics, potions, player/monster powers, orbs, even some custom tooltips from some mods. 
The viewers just need to hover over the respective item just as if they were in the game themselves.

See the extension config on Twitch for setup instructions (search 'Slay the Relics').
